               <p>JABEZ TROTMAN. I am <rs id="t18170917-13-deflabel72" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-13-defend147 t18170917-13-deflabel72"></join> at a lamp manufactory, in Long-acre. On the 10th of August, about nine o'clock in the evening, I was going home, and met the prisoner just by <placeName id="t18170917-13-crimeloc73">Ely-place, in Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-13-crimeloc73" type="placeName" value="Ely-place, in Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-13-crimeloc73" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-13-off70 t18170917-13-crimeloc73"></join>. I drew my watch out to see the time by the gas-light, and before I could replace it the prisoner snatched it from me-he<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181709170007"></xptr>kept walking by me, looking at it - He gave a sudden jerk, and it was gone instantly, but I could not see who he handed it to. He ran up Leather-lane, and was not out of my sight till I secured him, and took him to the watch-house, with assistance. I am positive he is the man. I have not recovered my watch.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ADOLPHUS. I was sober; there were several people about; he did not try to escape before he got to Leather-lane. He struggled to get away.</p>
               <p>JOSEPH MIETT. I am the watch-house keeper; the prisoner was brought to the watch-house. I found nothing on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18170917-13-verdict74" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18170917-13-verdict74" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 31.</p>
